# Build Bible V2 — Chapter 14 (Production Readiness)

Spec: `docs/16_BUILD_BIBLE_V2_CHAPTER_14_PRODUCTION_READINESS.md`

## Canonical ops docs

- Deploy: `docs/enterprise-deployment.md`
- Checklist: `docs/enterprise-release-checklist.md`
- Rollback: `docs/rollback-plan.md`
- DR: `docs/disaster-recovery.md`
- Env template: `.env.example` (Paddle-first)

## Rules

- Deployment preparation only — do not production-deploy, commit, or push from Chapter 14.
- Do not modify business logic, authentication, authorization, RBAC, RLS, Paddle billing behaviour, or API contracts.
- Do not execute production database migrations from this chapter.
- Keep secrets server-only; never add `NEXT_PUBLIC_` to service role, Paddle API, webhook, or cron secrets.
- Prefer updating canonical enterprise docs over proliferating versioned Stripe-era deploy notes.
- Production cron cadence must cover 5-minute jobs (`webhook_retries`, `queue_worker`).
- CI must gate on lint, typecheck, build, and production-readiness / regression suites.

## Abandoned configuration

- `BILLING_PROVIDER` is not a runtime switch — Paddle is sole active provider.
- Stripe env vars / `/api/stripe/*` must not be reintroduced as active paths.
